Description: Small amulet of clay, complete but unidentified shape, like a rough ib-heart but the thin horizontal perforation is at the base. The rear is flat, the front in relief. The clay shows fragments of lime and mica but no organic materials visible, not oxidized, so if fired, then in a low temperature.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D15, square P.A.3
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
